This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with proposing a new Quality Link Metric (QLM) in Optimized Link State Routing (OLSR) protocol for wireless multi-hop networks. It also compares the performance of existing QLMs based on loss probability measurements. Additionally, the paper discusses the enhancement of conventional OLSR to achieve high efficiency in terms of optimized routing load and routing latency. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT) as it involves the mathematical framework for validating the performance of the proposed QLM and the enhanced OLSR. 

The sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) is also a possibility as the paper may involve the use of machine learning techniques to optimize the routing load and latency in wireless multi-hop networks. 

The sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) is another possibility as the paper may discuss the security implications of the proposed QLM and the enhanced OLSR. 

Finally, the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) is also a possibility as the paper may involve the development of new algorithms for optimizing the routing load and latency in wireless multi-hop networks.
